It means you'll get to enjoy shows like Game Changer, Dimension 20, Make Some Noise, Very Important People, Um Actually, Dirty Laundry, and Breaking News. It means Dropout will be there for you whenever you need to laugh, unwind, or be blown away by a Brennan rant. And it means you'll pay practically nothing for it (we try to keep our price reasonable, we know these streaming service bills add up).

And for your very miniscule investment (basically the cost of a a sandwich once a month), you'll get SO much. With new content dropping nearly every day of the week, there's always new stuff to be discovering on Dropout - in addition to our extensive line-up of ongoing programming, you'll have access to a deep library of CollegeHumor sketches, behind-the-scenes content, and so much more.

History of Weapons and War brings together all the best independent experts on firearms history under one roof. If you want to learn about where different guns came from, how they were developed, where they were used, and how they work, this is the channel for you! With more than 6,000 videos covering firearms from the earliest matchlocks to the latest in high-tech developments, there is something here for everyone. 

Your hosts here include Ian McCollum, Jonathan Ferguson, Henry Chan, Balazs Nemeth, Matthew Moss, and more. From this wide group of subject matter experts you will see a variety of different specialties and perspectives on firearms history and their use. Working with museums like the British Royal Armouries, the best private collections, and shooting ranges around the world, we give you both the facts and the practical experience. 

From the standard weapons of the largest armies to the strangest prototypes and the most unusual experiments, it is all here waiting for
